Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getUPFPortAttr(25.10)                                    getUPFPortAttr(25.10)

Name
       getUPFPortAttr - Returns UPF port attributes from UPF or for the speci-
       fied values

Syntax
       getUPFPortAttr

       [-help]

       <hport_name>

       Returns  UPF  port attributes from UPF or for the specified values. Run
       this command before design partitioning. Following is the output format
       of this command:

       list of {attr_name val}

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information  for  each  getUPFPortAttr parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all its parameters, use  the  man
              command:

              man getUPFPortAttr

       <hport_name>
              Specifies  the  module  term  name for which UPF port attributes
              need to be returned.

Example
       The following command returns UPF port attributes for the iC/in hport:

       getUPFPortAttr iC/in

       Following is the output of the above command:

       {-driver_supply supplySetName} {attr_name value2} {is_analog FALSE} ...

Related Information
       Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

